# üêû bug report


### Description

In a component decorator, something like
```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: getHtml(),
  styles: [],
})
```
will work if `getHtml` is defined as something like
```ts
function getHtml(): string {
  return '<span>Test</span>';
}
```
BUT, if `getHtml` is defined as
```ts
function getHtml(): string {
  return [1,2,3].join();
}
```
you will get this error: `error NG1010: template must be a string`.

